                            <comment id="116352" author="nozaki" created="Tue, 26 May 2015 02:07:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I realized that LDLM_CANCEL doesn&apos;t have rq_no_resend and rq_no_delay in Lustre-2.x anymore !! so this patch isn&apos;t need.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="116218" author="adilger" created="Fri, 22 May 2015 17:12:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Could you please explain a bit more about where the &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;EWOULDBLOCK&lt;/tt&gt; error is coming from?  I see this in &lt;tt&gt;ptlrpc_import_delay_req()&lt;/tt&gt; but only if &lt;tt&gt;req-&amp;gt;rq_no_delay&lt;/tt&gt; is set.  Is &lt;tt&gt;rq_no_delay&lt;/tt&gt; being set in the &lt;tt&gt;LDLM_CANCEL&lt;/tt&gt; request somewhere?  I don&apos;t see it at first glance.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
